         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/1/92 ¶  ¶ Let me take the earliest opportunity, dear Mr Wilson, to thank the hon. the Chief Secretary and his hon. ministerial colleagues for the generous consideration, shown me in maintaining my ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.01.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">T92/2768, unit 663, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/1/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me take the earliest opportunity, dear Mr Wilson, to thank the hon. the Chief Secretary and his hon. ministerial colleagues for the generous consideration, shown me in maintaining my work and scientific dignity<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to T.Wilson, 27 January 1892.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and assure them, that I shall just as before give my whole time and thought and income, for maintaining the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">prestige</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the position, which Victoria has throughout maintained in the branch of scientific and applied knowledge, which I represent. As the Department becomes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">abolished</hi>
               </seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I presume the £400, mentioned in the Age as working expenses,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The passage from the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(Melbourne), 29 January 1892, p. 4, that M cites is: '</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">As has already be</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n stated in these columns, it</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>h</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">as been decided to abolish the department of .the Government botanist without making any</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">alteration in the duties or salary of its<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">h</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ead,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Baron von Mueller. That gentleman will retain his post as Government botanist<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">at</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a s</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ala</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ry</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">of £800 a year, and he will combine his scientific</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">researches and his work i</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>connection with his</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">herbarium as heretofore, the only stipulation</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">that the Government makes being that</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he total cost of the department</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">shall not ex</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ce</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ed £1200 p</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">r annum, so that</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">b</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">yond Baron von Mueller's salary a sum<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">o</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">f</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">£400 only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>will be available for expenditure.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will be a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">grant</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or allowance, so that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">cheapest</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>arrangements can be made,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to carry on the information, and so that no special transactions need<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">trouble</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>yourself as my superior officer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will wait on you some evening soon, to thank you personally for the powerful aid, by which I am now able to proceed in my scientific and utilitarian career unimpaired in my honor.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The file contains calculations by Wilson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for '<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Government Botanists Branch</hi>
                        </seg>'. The first shows the present annual expenditure as £2,865, comprising salaries at £1,705 and Contingencies at £1,160.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>That is followed by:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'[If] Branch be abolished, the following payments to be made<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Gratuities to</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Messrs Luehmann and Minchin who have not attained the age of 60 years non-recurring £<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">862.6.8</hi>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(The other Members of the Staff, are not entitled to a gratuity, in consequence of having joined the Service subsequent to the passing of Ramsay's Act.)'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He then calculated the remaining annual expenditure to be £1,020, made up as follows:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Estimated Annual Expenditure for maintaining the Botanic Museum, <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>say 500*</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pension to Baron von Mueller. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>520</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>*This, of course, is a mere guess. I presume the present Museum will have to be maintained somewhere and possibly the collection added to as heretofore</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: center; "
                        xml:lang="en">T.R.W.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: center; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>29/12/91'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 31 December 1891, the Chief Secretary, A. McLean, annotated the file: 'Abolish Office &amp; give 3 months notice'. However, on 28 January 1892, he minuted: 'Mueller to be [retained]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Total cost to be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>restricted to £<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #000000; ">12</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #000000; ">00</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>per annum [...] in writing.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Gratefully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
